- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks for a specific language, Yor\`ub\'a, and proposes a machine translation approach for diacritic restoration. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed approach uses Sequence-to-Sequence neural models, which are a popular machine learning technique for NLP tasks. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes an AI-based approach for diacritic restoration of Yor\`ub\'a text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper uses neural models for diacritic restoration. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper addresses the issue of limited device and application support for diacritics in electronic texts, which has implications for the use and preservation of minority languages and cultures.
